We need to have control over our devices. This idea sprung up from a mix of ad blocking thoughts and security/privacy. Rant about how all the big tech companies actually control our devices. But if we had control we could bring them to their knees. Turn them back into the product and not us.

Google noise - Destroy google's ability to make a profile of you by spamming them with noise that hides your real traffic.

A magic programming language - A novelty programming language that uses runes for characters (thanks unicode) and dramatic simplification to look and feel like magic.

Becoming better - I want to become a better programmer, but how does one go about that? Sports it always looked easy, just get bigger, stronger, tougher. But that isn't true is it. They have to think about their hold ups and figure out how to go beyond them.
